Package soot.toDex.instructions

Class Insn21t

  • java.lang.Object
    • soot.toDex.instructions.AbstractInsn
      • soot.toDex.instructions.InsnWithOffset
        • soot.toDex.instructions.Insn21t
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, Insn, OneRegInsn
    public class Insn21t
extends InsnWithOffset
implements OneRegInsn
    The "21t" instruction format: It needs two 16-bit code units, has one register and is used for jump targets (hence the "t").

    It is used e.g. by the opcode "if-eqz" for conditional jumps to a 16-bit wide offset.
